Iranian students are willing to die for their country's nuclear program.
They formed a human shield.
Several hundred university students formed human shields around nuclear facilities in Iran.
With his gesture, they want to express their support for his country's nuclear programme in the face of a possible Israeli attack.
The students started praying Tuesday at noon before the facilities and then chorused death slogans to the US and Israel.
Several hundred university students trained on Tuesday in the Iranian city of Isfahan human shields around the nuclear technology centre in which uranium works.
They seek to demonstrate that they are willing to defend their country's nuclear program with their own lives.
The International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA), in a recent report, found that Iran, according to all indications, strives to achieve nuclear weapons.
There is talk in Israel about a possible attack on Iranian nuclear facilities.
The students began to pray at noon at the Isfahan nuclear facilities and then launched death slogans against the United States and Israel.
