Daily menu of an obese child: not breakfast and supper embroidered
More than one third of children between the ages of 9 and 13 have overweight problems, where overweight affects 9 per cent of the school population and obesity 5 per cent.
Obese children come in most families with a non-healthy lifestyle, according to current research.
It is demonstrated again the importance of the environment where it grows for a healthy development of the person, as well as the models that serve as a reference.
On the table, obsessed children feed, for example, at least twice as often as children from normal-weight families.
For dinner, more than 19% of the obese had eaten fried potatoes the day before the analysis, which is linked to the prevention program " obesity is not a coincidence".
In the families of overweight children, there is no habit of sports, which applies to most of the current families, where only 15 per cent of the children responded that their parents, at least once a week, find time for physical exercise.
Survey of 900 children
The survey was carried out at the end of last school year and involved nearly 900 children in basic education throughout the Czech Republic.
It was already the second edition of the program "The obesity of not a coincidence", which supports the General Health Insurance Company and the Unilever company.
So far, more than 12,000 children have participated in the project from 4th to 8th grade.
An adequate diet and fairly exercise in the family are determining factors, which significantly reduce the number of overweight and even obesity children.
"Only half of the children surveyed have responded that they have five meals per day according to the regime: breakfast, lunch, food, snack and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet," he collects one of the results of the survey.
No breakfast but with supper sausage
Specialists warn that, in a healthy development, the details, which also count, are important, such as having a fixed hour for family breakfast.
In Czech Republic, however, only 23 per cent of schoolchildren's families have breakfast at the same time.
In most families, each has breakfast alone.
But the worst thing was to find out that 10 percent of the households don't eat anything for breakfast.
Breakfast is, however, the basis of a correct daily diet.
The study shows that the families of obese children are much more often consumed with unhealthy fries.
Almost all - regardless of weight - drink daily sweet drinks (70%).
In general, more than 40 per cent of the children surveyed are sporting, however, among their parents this result is reduced to less than half, only 15 per cent.
Register your diet
The next phase of the study made it possible for the chosen boys (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to create their own diets based on all possible offers according to their tastes and opinions.
"The food preferences of Czech children between the ages of 12 and 15, from the point of view of healthy food, are far from ideal."
Among your favorite foods are pasta, meat and sweets
"It is especially alarming the popularity of sweet drinks," the study's final report notes.
As a main meal the palm is taken the pasta and closely follows the poultry meat.
Practically, children always reject legume and taste for fish and vegetables is very low.
Change to healthy habits
At the same time, the study shows that children are willing to change their eating habits if they receive just information.
"In the control group of the study participants, who completed the questionnaire after the completion of the prevention program "Obesity is not a coincidence", an important change was made in many cases in favour of the principles of healthy food", is pointed out in the results of the study.
It draws attention, for example, to sweet drinks, where many children would begin to prefer normal and current water.
Children would also choose more frequently in the questionnaire poultry meat and fish for main food and restrict the consumption of sweet food and flour derivatives.
