En Need for Speed: The Run competes throughout America.
Review
A trip, in principle careless, is complicated by a series of improper neglects of a routine trip during tomorrow's shift.
To a certain extent, the expectations were met, but that was no use, if, in fact, it was not intended to do anything extraordinary.
The new delivery, to which the title is added The Run, awakened great expectations already before its premiere.
He promised that he would give new air to the old racing saga Need for Speed and, as a result of what was shown, he appears as a game that should not end up being again a genre of action without more.
We were also curious to know how the inserted scenes would remain, where the main character descends from the car and walks through his own foot.
As often happens in the NFS series, the results do not vary much with regard to what we expected.
There are careers that can be given for acceptable, but in total counting points are lost because of absurd failures, which have already appeared in the series for years.
In reality, errors cannot be called, but rather the incomprehensible deviation of programmers.
The adventure begins very well.
You are introduced to a story, whose protagonist, Jack, has certain personal problems; to solve them, you are offered to participate in an illegal career throughout America.
You sit on the steering wheel on the west coast, in San Francisco, and your mission is to reach the first in New York.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than fifty races.
It follows that each race takes place on a different route and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite diverse and interesting.
In this way, one does not remotely feel that the game always offers the same.
Some of the environments are even pleasant to see, although the technical level of the chart is equivalent to previous delivery of the series.
So, it's nothing from the other world.
But the stroll through the desert, the autumn landscape or the high snowy mountains produce a very pleasant visual effect.
In addition, careers are diversified from time to time by an atypical element.
So, for example, in the desert you find yourself a sand storm that decreases visibility.
Instead, in the mountains you must be careful not to bury an avalanche.
According to that, each of the races is very well developed.
There's only a couple of models, but that's enough.
For a moment, you try to advance a number of required rivals (normally in a classical race), then you try to earn time (timed classical flat) and then await a duel against a single opponent.
In the midst of all this the police sometimes appear, which does nothing but make things even more difficult.
The novelty is the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape someone and you have to help him, always pressing the button right at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are quite fewer landscapes in the game than could be expected (in particular there are only three).
But the final result is positive, because this element does not become annoying and, in the context already mentioned, it is one of the elements that make the game more interesting.
The driving model follows the footprints of the previous episodes.
That means that today is no longer a big deal, but it cannot be said to be bad.
If you're looking for a realistic simulation, you can look somewhere else.
But a career designed with enough action suits quite this driving style, although we can find something better among the games of the competition.
So far, everything's in order.
But the problems arise after a certain time.
Unlike the right driving models, the same is no longer the case with collisions.
From such games you can't expect to rebuild complicated deformations and collisions, but in fact before a blow on any object, you can't predict how your car will react, so not everything is in order.
It is typical that, by making a very tight advance or circulating the car with a normal traffic, there are only light sprays, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up making uncontrolled pyrouettes.
Or even it ends up completely destroyed.
Thanks to the reset system, there are no big problems, but it can make you feel bad.
The resets are programmed so that when you have an accident or get out of the track, the game returns you to the last rescue point on the track.
However, only five resettlements are available in each race.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it's just a help in case something goes wrong, but it's not very reliable.
Sometimes, not even the reset helps, it only helps to learn the given stage of memory.
A great disadvantage of the game is that the same facts are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, you have to enter in a specific way; otherwise they are impossible to take.
Other times you find yourself somewhere "civil" vehicles always with the same configuration, even if you are the first, fifth or you arrived five minutes before or after.
This makes it rage especially in situations, when you see that two cars going to meet in opposite directions, your opponent moves forward without problems, but when you arrive, you must turn or either slow down.
It's the same when you get here, because it's programmed because the "surprise" will always happen in front of your noses.
The opponents also have one more advantage.
Throughout the game you will arrive at places where, without taking into account the time, the same opponent will always advance you on the same site.
In addition, this happens at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must come before you, whatever price it is.
When it goes ahead of you, it makes it difficult for you to see the cars coming from the front, so at first you can papilla the car.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum suspense and adrenaline doses, but the execution is so apparent that it will surely disappoint you immediately.
And it's a pity, because even though the model of the trip is simple, the game is fun and with action, so it is often not possible to follow in detail what happens or where.
And it really matters, if merit takes the idea with fifty exclusive tracks or the ranking in the race so that it doesn't fit the boredom, or anything else.
An unusual idea is the change of cars during the races.
You have to be attentive to the gasoline suppliers next to the road, because right there you have to change your car, although in the vast majority of cases what you have will be enough for you.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports are suitable for urban areas, strong American cars for straight highways and super-sport exotics for technical driving, for example by mountain roads with curves.
In addition, the main narrative thread also appears a thread of parallel challenges, i.e. there are careers in specific places that you will know by the stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also points of experience for your profile, which serves both challenges and stories.
Upon reaching the top level, the driver opens up several possibilities, starting with the car and finishing up with profile funds.
At the same time, there is connected an online Autolog function, which compares your results with those of other players and provides other community functions.
One of the hardest elements to understand is how the last race in history is made.
With the car you arrive to the subway tunnel (pass), where you get to run darkly along the tracks (pass).
The speed meter marks you between 150 and 200 km/h (pass) and, suddenly, the metro convoy arrives behind you and takes you ahead without more.
In the writing we will surely have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the programming of the game none even thought a little bit or if the real authors take us for a bunch of fools.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the general visual effects result in most pleasant cases, sometimes even sovereign.
What a pity that, at the most tense moments, the quality of image is reduced and sometimes severely.
This mainly affects accidents where many participants are involved, when continuous image quality is no longer valid.
The audio is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In order to please most of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the category "each of his father and mother", but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game just for his music.
The final feeling of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore quite confusing.
If the game avoided absolutely silly mistakes, we would have trouble claiming that The Run is the best NFS game in recent years.
It gives the feeling that the game is not finished.
The fun is secured, but prepare because the mistakes will hit you in the eyes with the strength of some airport reflectors.
The coroners of the Carolina University will participate in the concert "Students of Terciopelo".
The joint celebration of the International Students' Day and the anniversary of the Terciopelo Revolution as a musical experience will take place for the third time at the Festa Academica festival.
During this year, 20 corals will be presented from secondary and university centres.
The festival revolves around two concerts on November 17.
"The Carolina University has a high participation in the festival."
Among the present choirs are the coral of the Faculty of Pedagogy and the Faculty of Humanities, in the festival committee is Rector Václav Hampl," said the organization's director, Jakub Čaloun.
The summit of the whole festival is the free entrance for all public to the concert of the high school choirs, which will be held on 17 March at 14 hours in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The program includes the participation of the Czech jazzist Karel Ręžička and his Celebration Jazz Mass.
In the evening the concert "Students of Terciopelo" will be held at the venues of the Municipal House in Vynohrady, in which university corals will participate, including the choir of the Carolina University.
The Academic Festival aims not only to honor the International Students' Day and to remember the 22nd anniversary of the Terciopelo Revolution, but also to present to the public the coral music at the highest level and to promote collaborative creation among young people.
The main organizer is the Czech Union of Corales in collaboration with the Jan Kepler Secondary Institute.
All the events were supported by the mayor of Prague, Bohuslav Svoboda, and the rector of the Carolina University, Václav Hampl.
The Festival will take place between 16 and 20 November between Prague and Pardubice.
The calendar offers, in addition to celebratory concerts, a whole series of musical events, improvised student shows and morning concerts.
More information can be found on the festival page www.festariacademica.cz
