How to detect a lie
A look at the most recent headlines tells us how serious and omnipresent are deception and lies in daily life.
The Republican presidential candidate Herman Cain is busy exchanging allegations of sexual harassment with several women; each party charges lying to the other.
The administrators of the State University of Pennsylvania have been charged with perjury for allegedly hiding reports saying that a retired football coach was sexually assaulting children.
